               <p>PHOEBE MOULD. I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18220703-88-person775">
                  Thomas 
                  Mould
               <interp inst="t18220703-88-person775" type="surname" value="Mould"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-88-person775" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-88-person775" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who is a <rs id="t18220703-88-viclabel461" type="occupation">wharfinger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-88-victim774 t18220703-88-viclabel461"></join> in Mr. Pickford's employ. On the 14th of June, about a quarter to nine o'clock at night, I went to meet my husband - and as I returned saw the prisoner in the passage with these things in his hand. We live in <placeName id="t18220703-88-crimeloc462">John's-row, St. Luke's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-88-crimeloc462" type="placeName" value="John's-row, St. Luke's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-88-crimeloc462" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-88-off459 t18220703-88-crimeloc462"></join>; I called Stop thief! he threw them down. I had left the street door open, and my boy in bed, but he was asleep. The prisoner had got in through the back window; he was stopped before I lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>
            
